HEADWORD: Emblazonry
<hw>Em*bla"zon*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Emblazonries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The act or art of an
emblazoner; heraldic or ornamental decoration, as pictures or figures on
shields, standards, etc.; emblazonment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thine ancient standard's rich <qex>emblazonry</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

